ollowers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/schiesbn/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/schiesbn/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/schiesbn/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/schiesbn/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/schiesbn/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/schiesbn/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/schiesbn/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/schiesbn/received_events","type":"user","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2013-10-18t10:19:52z","updated_at":"2013-10-18t10:21:00z","body":"> that account had encryption enabled and now the login screen tells me that the password is wrong. \r\n\r\nthe encryption app doesn't create such a message. the encryption app only gets triggered after you successfully logged in.\r\n\r\nnormally the upgrade shouldn't disable the encryption app. you could check the oc_appconfig table if the encryption app is still enabled: ```select * from oc_appconfig  where appid=\"files_encryption\" and configkey=\"enabled\";``` but as said, at the moment i doubt that this has something to do with the encryption app. if it is enabled you could also try to disable it to see if the login works without the encryption app.\r\n\r\nplease also check your owncloud.log or apache error log to see if they provide any useful information?\r\n\r\nhow you might be able to solve the problem:\r\nyou could try to login with the new adim and set the user password in the user management again. (use the same password you used before).\r\n"},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/comments/30009659","html_url":"https://github.com/owncloud/core/issues/4455#issuecomment-30009659","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/4455","id":30009659,"user":{"login":"karlitschek","id":867445,"avatar_url":"https://gravatar.com/avatar/87ce2b4531e